  "title": "Claim Arrangement",
  "description": "A Claim Arrangement is an agreed commitment between the insurer and the policyholder (or beneficiary) to perform specific actions that fulfill the claim-related obligations under a Funeral Policy Agreement, when a covered event occurs.\r\nIs an Arrangement to submit, register, and initiate the processing of a claim for funeral benefits under a Funeral Policy agreement.\r\nIn an insurance contract, a claim arrangement refers to the agreed-upon process and procedures for submitting, verifying, and settling claims when a covered event occurs. It is essentially the operational part of the contract that shows how the policyholder or beneficiary can access the benefits promised by the insurer.\r\n\r\nA Claim Arrangement is the configuration that defines how claims will be handled under a specific funeral policy_ including the claim rules, channels, entitlements, documents, and participants involved before any actual claim occurs.",
